aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1801 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CIV is testing instances of Salesforce to determine whether AI features would make it easier for our litigators to organize their case files.

Expected benefits: Time savings over manual categorization. Files are organized into cases for user review"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1802 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_4,  # Customer experience, satisfaction, and retention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Intelligent Bot tool is implemented using Question and Answer (QnA) Maker and the Language Understanding (LUIS) services which is developed using the Microsoft Azure Software As A Service (SAAS) infrastructure in the Cloud on the COPS website.  

Expected benefits: This will allow COPS to easily implement a brand new knowledge base of questions and answers feature on the site which will respond via a chat box based on a question entered by the customer. Response"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1803 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: BMC Helix's ITSM AI capabilities include Proactive Problem Management and Incident Correlation, which will allow CRM's IT Service Desk to more efficiently identify issues, resolve incidents, automate case routing, and perform root cause analysis. 

Expected benefits: Increase IT service desk productivity, prevent issues before they occur, and decrease user downtime. Prediction, recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1804 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CLEAR LPR enables investigators to identify location history for license plates, connect addresses and individuals of interest to a vehicle's location and obtain images of a vehicle. CRM uses CLEAR LPR to aid in investigations. 

Expected benefits: Streamline investigations, reducing the need to search multiple platforms, while saving costs and allowing investigators to more quickly identify relevant information. Object recognition, OCR, prediction"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1805 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_3,  # Innovation pace and responsiveness
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText "CMS's Child Exploitation and Obscenity Section used Clearview fewer than five times in 2020 as part of evaluating and experimenting with the software. CEOS stopped using Clearview almost immediately after obtaining it, because of a reported data breach within Clearview. CEOS no longer has a Clearview license, is not using it, and does not plan to use it again. N/A; not in use"^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1806 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CRM uses Veritone to convert speech in audio or video files into text transcripts.

Expected benefits: Transcribe audio and video, saving manual review time and associated costs. Transcription"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1807 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: AI could be used in ArcGIS Pro for identification of "Clustering", "Regression", and "Classification" of a wide variety of types of spatial data.  AI could be useful for identifying discriminatory patterns or practices in bank loan lending, student attendance zone anomalies, disability compliance or a wide variety of criminal activities. This tool's AI features are not in use.

Expected benefits: AI implementation in geospatial software (ArcGIS Pro) would have direct benefits to DOJ CRT's mission.  It would speed up customer wait time by automating many of the geospatial processes that were previously done manually.  It would increase more comprehensive map/outputs by allowing AI to assess the geospatial data more thoroughly than a human could.  AI would also provide customers with more options for illustrating their output on maps, such that the customer can secure the map(s) that best represent the point they are trying to make for any given matter. No output. The AI capabilities are available but not used or configured. Activation of these capabilities would require downloading special folders."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1808 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_4,  # Scaling operations without degrading quality or CX
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To enable network routing technology to optimize speed of routing and re-route traffic around any configuration issues.

Expected benefits: Helps sustain reliable networks access to CRT networked infrastructure by CRT staff. Decision and action relating to network routing and load management."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1809 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To enable network routing technology to optimize speed of routing and re-route traffic around any configuration issues.

Expected benefits: Helps sustain reliable networks access to CRT networked infrastructure by CRT staff. Decision and action relating to network routing and load management."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1810 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Dynamic captions uses AI tech within the local client software to convert speech to text and produce a transcript file. This tool's AI features are not in use.  

Expected benefits:  The captioning is used based on user  preference within their client app.  The feature for production and retention of transcripts is disabled by CRT IT Policy. No output.  The transcription saving is disabled."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1811 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To automate the disqualification of reports not submitted by a human but submitted by bots.  This tool monitors submissions by bots and may eventually block that bot-associated IP addresses from submitting reports.

Expected benefits: Saves pre-processing time by CRT staff and only routes actionable reports within the routing workflow. Decision related to routing of a civil rights violation report submitted by a bot."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1812 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Use natural language processing to convert spoken audio to text for employees with vision or mobility limitations.

Expected benefits: Increased accessibility. Employees with a disability are provided a solution to accommodate their reasonable accommodation for Section 508 obligations. Text transcription of spoken audio."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1813 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CRT uses the auto-transcribe feature to transcribe body worn camera footage to text making it more easily searchable.   CRT also uses the redaction assistant feature to remove sensitive information from videos.

Expected benefits: Improved speed of pre-processing workflows, faster identification of relevant audio, efficiency of investigations. text transcriptions, video with sensitive images redacted"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1814 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_6_2,  # Engagement, culture, and incentives
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CRT uses an AI feature to convert speech to text and produce a transcript file. This tool's AI features are not in use. 

Expected benefits:  The captioning is used based on user preference within their client app.  The producing and retaining a transcript is disabled by CRT IT Policy. No output.  The transcription saving is disabled."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1815 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Understanding the manufacturing origin and distribution route of illicit drugs by analyzing the chemical composition of seized drugs is a core DEA task. The purpose of this use case is to use AI/ML techniques to develop, maintain, and improve models that enable designated forensic chemists to identify a notional geographic origin or notional manufacturing route of samples selected for DEA's Drug Signature Programs.

Expected benefits: The solution supports designated forensic chemists at DEA to automate analyses and to more quickly identify trend changes regarding drug sample notional geographic origin or notional manufacturing route. Designated forensic chemists responsible for a particular Signature Program are provided with the model's output - a notional geographic region of origin or a notional manufacturing route of samples -- which these forensic chemists then evaluate along with other available information to better understand drug trends."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1816 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities. It requires a deep understanding of drug markets, manufacturing, and distribution channels. License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases.

Expected benefits: License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases. This License Plate Reader (LPR) technology captures images of vehicle license plates, automatically converts the information they contain to characters, and can add metadata such as the time and location the image was captured."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1817 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_1_1,  # Direction, ambition, and coherence
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities. It requires a deep understanding of drug markets, manufacturing, and distribution channels. License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases.

Expected benefits: License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases. This License Plate Reader (LPR) technology captures images of vehicle license plates, automatically converts the information they contain to characters, and can add metadata such as the time and location the image was captured."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1818 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_1_1,  # Direction, ambition, and coherence
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities. It requires a deep understanding of drug markets, manufacturing, and distribution channels. License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases.

Expected benefits: License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases. This License Plate Reader (LPR) technology captures images of vehicle license plates, automatically converts the information they contain to characters, and can add metadata such as the time and location the image was captured."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1819 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_1_1,  # Direction, ambition, and coherence
        aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities. It requires a deep understanding of drug markets, manufacturing, and distribution channels. License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases.

Expected benefits: License Plate Readers (LPR) can be one important investigative tool to support cases. This License Plate Reader (LPR) technology captures images of vehicle license plates, automatically converts the information they contain to characters, and can add metadata such as the time and location the image was captured."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1820 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities and save lives. The purpose of this use case is to compare friction ridge prints to other prints within the boundaries of a case. 

Expected benefits: To assist in friction ridge analyses, which can save significant amount of time and resources. It can standardize DEA's friction ridge program and reduce missed identification errors. Outputs images and portions of print cards."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1821 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities and save lives. DEA's Forensic Sciences Division receives tens of thousands of diverse drug seizures (e.g. drug form, shapes, sizes, counts) annually. The purpose of this use case is for forensic chemists to utilize object detection as a second validation step. 

Expected benefits: To ensure timely high confidence of counts, this use case allows forensic scientists to accelerate validation and enables quality control checks by serving as a unbiased count against submitted paperwork and manual counts. This will reduce a labor and resource intensive counting process. Outputs recommended counts with image labels."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1822 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities and save lives. DEA has dedicated personnel to review the proposed AI-generated redactions of extracted video files. Redactions are applied to a copy of the original file to ensure the raw files are not altered in the process.

Expected benefits: To further DEA's mission of protecting American communities, this allows dedicated DEA personnel to review proposed relevant footage, resulting in time and cost savings. In addition, this solution helps standardize the audio/visual redaction process to produce video evidence connected to judicial processes and FOIA requests. Outputs include proposed redactions and text transcriptions of audio and video footage that require a dedicated DEA personnel to review, possibly adjust, and approve recommendations."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1823 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_2,  # Market understanding, demand estimation, and segmentation
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3,  # Automation and AI enablement
        aiu:BG_9_3 ;  # Resilience to geopolitical, pandemic, and disaster shocks
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA has a mission to protect communities and save lives. It requires an understanding of global drug markets, manufacturing, and distribution channels as well as the impact of illicit drugs on communities and individuals. Supply chain analytics is a tool to further drug trafficking investigations and protecting the American public.

Expected benefits: Supply chain information can further investigative leads and allow dedicated DEA personnel to better understand the impact and trends of drug markets. Supply chain analytical outputs vary by query and generally focus on specific markets or business entities."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1824 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA is a data-driven organization that integrates data and analytics capabilities across its mission. The purpose of this use case is to search, monitor, and analyze wide variety of public-facing unstructured and structured data sources such as scientific literature, social media, dark web, news, public records, public internet forums, and more to protect American communities and save lives. 

Expected benefits: This use case enables DEA to gain key insights at exponentially higher speeds with lower costs by fusing variety of data sources. Benefits include: operational insights, emerging threat detection, agent safety, public safety, improved mission-enabling services, etc. Outputs vary by use case."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1825 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: DEA is a data-driven organization that integrates data and analytics capabilities across its mission. The purpose of this use case is to search, monitor, and analyze wide variety of public-facing unstructured and structured data sources such as scientific literature, social media, dark web, news, public records, public internet forums, and more to protect American communities and save lives. 

Expected benefits: This use case enables DEA to gain key insights at exponentially higher speeds with lower costs by fusing variety of data sources. Benefits include: operational insights, emerging threat detection, agent safety, public safety, improved mission-enabling services, etc. Outputs vary by use case."""^^xsd:string .

