aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1886 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Program uses character recognition to read and identify license plates. 

Expected Benefits: License plate reader technology assists in locating vehicles associated with persons of interest. License plate values"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1887 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To provide NCIC with a more accurate name matching algorithm that is currently in production.

Expected benefits: The models can produce much quicker searches on word embeddings than they would otherwise be able to do, and can generate a larger return of similar phrases or misspellings. The output of the search algorithm is composed of both the AI components, external products, and NCIC-established parameters."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1888 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: N-DEx uses natural language processing (NLP) service that uses machine learning to uncover valuable insights and connections in the text of criminal justice and law enforcement related information in the system. N-DEx is used to perform this extraction by training models using data that contain that person or entity. 

Expected benefits: The benefit of this use case is to provide an entity extraction feature to aid N-DEx searches so that users can accurately search for people and filter the search results based on a specified role type. Entity extraction such as person objects and addresses."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1889 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Produce faster searches of databases of state laws relevant to a NICS background check.

Expected benefits: The models can produce much quicker searches on word embeddings than they would otherwise be able to do, and can generate a larger return of similar phrases or misspellings. The AI model facilitates more accurate and wider-ranged search responses for NICS analysts when they examine state law databases for laws relevant to a NICS background check."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1890 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To provide NGI with a more accurate biometrics capabilities, including name matching algorithm, provide finger print matching,  facial recognition, iris recognition, and latent print matching.

Expected benefits: Increased accuracy. Investigative leads"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1891 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Threat Intake Processing System (TIPS) database uses AI algorithms to accurately identify, prioritize, and process actionable tips in a timely manner. The AI used in this case helps to triage immediate threats in order to help FBI field offices and law enforcement respond to the most serious threats first. Based on the algorithm score, highest priority tips are first in the queue for human review.

Expected benefits: The AI used in this case helps to triage immediate threats in order to help FBI field offices A score that shows the probability of a threat. Key Phrase and Entity Extraction."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1892 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Tool to conduct authorized searches of photos of individuals pertinent to an ongoing investigation against publicly available images to generate investigative leads.

Expected benefits: generation of investigative leads -"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1893 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_2,  # Cybersecurity and protection
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Tool provides capabilities to support data and analytics, data synthesis, filtering, and linking of open source & threat intelligence.

Expected benefits: increased analytic capability -"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1894 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Adobe Acrobat uses Optical Character Recognition (OCR) of scanned documents and indexes which can be searched to quickly locate information and process multiple FOIA and Privacy Act requests.

Expected benefits: Efficiency and cost savings. The AI tool allows employees to search for and find information quicker than manual processes would allow. Provides areas to search for multiple requests."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1895 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This application was used to check for grammatical errors and spelling. The application can also suggest verbiage, paraphrase content, and change tone. 

Expected benefits: Improved written communications; increased efficiency in drafting communications. Suggestions on what verbiage to include to improve clarity."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1896 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This application was used to check for grammatical errors and spelling. The application can also generate and translate text.

Expected benefits: Improved written communications; increased efficiency in drafting communications. Suggestions on what verbiage to use to improve clarity."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1897 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The ASCVD is used as a preventative measure to identify inmates that are at risk for heart disease in order to provide more aggressive treatment to reduce that risk.

Expected benefits: The expected outcome would be to have less heart disease or related complications due to the proactive assessment of potential risk. An estimated percentage of the possibility of the inmate developing heart disease over the next ten years and over the inmate's lifetime."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1898 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Automated Medication Dispensing Cabinet uses a fingerprint scanner in order to provide faster and more secure login of users.

Expected benefits: To prevent unauthorized access to the medications held in the cabinets. Decides if the fingerprint scanned matches the one in the system for each specific employee."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1899 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_5_2,  # Cost structure and inflation resilience
        aiu:BG_6_1,  # Talent, skills, and workforce strategy
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This analytical tool is used for assessing staffing levels within the Federal Bureau of Prisons. 

Expected benefits: The expected benefit of the AI use case is to maximize cost effectiveness of staffing needs for each institution. Output reports provide how many positions are currently authorized within the FBOP."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1900 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_4,  # Customer experience, satisfaction, and retention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Provide learners with data driven course work in Aztec Learning Management System (LMS).

Expected benefits: Improved learning experiences. Predictions and reports of trends."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1901 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Uses statistical techniques to predict misconduct for newly admitted inmates. In turn, this prediction is used to assign appropriate security levels.

Expected benefits: Correctly classifying inmates' security level will decrease the level of misconduct towards other inmates and staff. AUC score showing the degree to which the instrument correctly discriminates between those who commit misconduct and those who do not."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1902 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The systems enable FBOP employees to configure the environmental conditions, including AI-enabled security features.

Expected benefits: Reduce energy consumption and waste, monitor performance, and alerts for device failures. Alerts"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1903 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_6_2,  # Engagement, culture, and incentives
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool was used to improve the quality of written communication, emails, and fliers to notify staff on institution updates.

Expected benefits: Improvements in the quality of written communications. Recommendations on grammar and communication formats"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1904 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This is an FBOP-developed tool to identify individuals due to be released to the community who require clinical review for additional treatment services once released into pre-release confinement.

Expected benefits: Reduces clinical reviews by a third by pre-screening those with no indicators of potential treatment needs in FBOP records management systems (SENTRY or BEMR). Checkmarks for potential types of treatment needs found in SENTRY or BEMR."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1905 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_6_1,  # Talent, skills, and workforce strategy
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool  synchronizes audio files to video. 

Expected benefits: Video to be used for communications and training purposes. Output is an video file (e.g., MP4)"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1906 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_1_4,  # Strategic planning and scaling under uncertainty
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: FBOP takes a strategic planning approach to managing our agency. FBOP regularly reviews capacity requirements, considers the current and projected inmate population levels, current law enforcement initiatives, geographic origin of the confined population, and the age and condition of existing facilities.  The FBOP strives to manage the existing large population and resulting crowding, at higher security levels, to ensure that federal inmates continue to serve their sentences in a safe and humane environment. AI was used to assist in inmate population projections, helping FBOP achieve these goals. This AI use case assisted with the projection of estimated inmate populations for up to 4 years. 

Expected benefits: Benefits included the provision of information for agency budgeting and physical capacity planning to meet our strategic goals, such as: ensuring that FBOP appropriately cares for and houses those in our custody; continuing to operate a high quality, cost effective, and innovative health care system; developing environments which better mirror our communities; advancing technology in support of the agency's mission; and reviewing and analyzing data to inform evidence-based decisions that will be used to improve agency operations. Aggregate level counts of inmates projected to be in agency's custody as of end of each future fiscal year, for the upcoming 4 years"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1907 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This application was used to check for grammatical errors. The application can also generate content. 

Expected benefits: To help improve the clarity and grammar of written communications. Recommendations on grammar and communication formats"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1908 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_4,  # Alignment with stakeholder expectations and social impact
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Staff have periodically used Google Translate to translate documents and notifications for the Spanish speaking population from English to Spanish.

Expected benefits: Translating documents from English to Spanish allows for the Spanish speaking population the opportunity to stay well informed with the events and details of the institution. Google translate provides a word for word translation of the information entered."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1909 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool was used to improve the quality of written communication.

Expected benefits: Better written communications. Recommendations on grammar and communication formats"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1910 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Data entered is analyzed to determine if an inmate needs a medical procedure.

Expected benefits: To streamline and assist in medical procedure decisions. Provides a decision option, however, a medical doctor can chose to use the decision provided or override it."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1911 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: FBOP uses Quantum Choice to adjudicate medical claims and analyze system data.

Expected benefits: Cost savings and increased compliance with billing regulations and contract pricing terms.  It also provides data analysis to assist with the FBOP's mission. Medical Billing Payment decisions are made utilizing the AI."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1912 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Initial assessment of medical and mental health care levels.

Expected benefits: Reducing the time to determine a final medical and mental health care level. A medical and mental health care level score (1-4)"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1913 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Uses statistical techniques to classify text descriptions of arrests.

Expected benefits: Accurate classification of arrests records and proper monitoring of recidivism. Classifies arrests into offense types"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1914 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_6_1,  # Talent, skills, and workforce strategy
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To assist FBOP employees with career pathways. The system generates assessments based on user input.  It scores the assessments taken to provide a user with options for career pathways.

Expected benefits: Improved understanding of career pathways. Provides employees with career recommendations based on assessments."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1915 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool, developed by OJP, uses pre-defined rules to score an inmate's recidivism risk level.

Expected benefits: PATTERN provides a standardized approach to calculating a recidivism risk level. A recidivism risk score."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1916 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Psychological test interpretation assistance.

Expected benefits: Assistance during psychological evaluations and treatment planning. Interpretive reports."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1917 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_2,  # Cybersecurity and protection
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: FBOP uses reCAPTCHA to distinguish between a human and bot request to determine whether to allow the request to be submitted via email to the FOIA office.

Expected benefits: It provides verification and security to  website. Determination of whether the request is coming from a human or bot to allow the request to be submitted via email to the FOIA office."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1918 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Static-99 is used as one data point in a 10 point manual process to evaluate FBOP sex offender's risk for recidivism. The tool uses pre-defined rules to score an inmate's recidivism risk level.

Expected benefits: To assist the evaluator in the recidivism risk review process by providing a key data point used in the overall evaluation. A score indicating the inmate's risk for recidivism of a sexual offense."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1919 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Software includes predictive procedures, modeling procedures, forecasting, text analytics, natural language processing, and other AI capabilities. FBOP uses this tool to analyze data and provide assessments that affect decisions made by FBOP.

Expected benefits: More efficient data analysis. Recommendations from data analysis"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1920 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_7_3,  # Contract management and intellectual-property stewardship
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: FBOP uses Thomson Reuters Drafting Assistant tool in MS Word to help with the drafting of legal documents. 

Expected benefits: Better written communications. Prediction and recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1921 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Tests suspected incoming mail for narcotics. 

Expected benefits: Confirmation of staff visual identification of narcotic introduction through institution mail. Reports"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1922 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Security feature that allows only a particular adult in custody (AIC) access to their individual account. Uses biometric (fingerprints and vocal) identification.

Expected benefits: Secure access Decision: If their biometrics matches, the inmate can gain access to their information."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1923 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool uses AI functionality to search for relevant information within various FBOP systems.

Expected benefits: To assist with the FBOP's mission by completing assessments and analysis of FBOP systems for investigative purposes. Provides users with actionable information for investigative purposes."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1924 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Detects and analyzes UAS near FBOP facilities to determine if the UAS is a threat to an institution. Provides reliable threat detection as part of FBOPs overall mission to provide safe and secure facilities. 

Expected benefits: To maintain security of FBOP institutions. The benefits of such detections serve FBOPs mission to protect society by confining offenders in the controlled environments of prisons and community-based facilities that are safe and appropriately secure. Outputs provide UAS identification and location information."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1925 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool is used in research for clinical practice guidance.  The user can submit a condition and the tool compiles a list of treatments and information that is currently being recommended in the medical field.

Expected benefits: Improved patient outcomes Information, summaries, links to published peer-reviewed research, and treatments."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1926 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: FBOP uses Veritone software to redact videos and phone call transcripts to respond to FOIA requests for such items. The software uses AI to redact facial images and other potentially sensitive information. After the AI tool completes its initial review, a FOIA employee must still review videos frame by frame and transcripts in their entirety to ensure all information requiring redaction was completed and redacts items the AI tool missed. 

Expected benefits: Using AI saves countless hours of employee time, places BOP in a better position to both respond to FOIA requests and meet court imposed litigation deadlines, and ultimately saves the government money. Recommendation: what to redact. It is not a decision since an employee must still review each frame of video / a full transcript and make necessary modifications."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1927 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_1,  # Brand positioning, identity, and value communication
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This AI tool converts text to speech audio that is used in social media, training videos, and audiobooks

Expected benefits: Audio to be used for communications and training purposes. Output is an audio file (e.g., MP3)"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1928 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: System can detect intruders while minimizing false alarms.

Expected benefits: Increased security FBOP institutions. Alerts about movement for an employee to follow up with a live visual of the area."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1929 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3,  # Automation and AI enablement
        aiu:BG_9_3 ;  # Resilience to geopolitical, pandemic, and disaster shocks
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Exiger DDIQ leverages natural language processing (NLP), machine learning (ML), and AI-powered analytics to enhance due diligence processes by continuously ingesting and analyzing structured and unstructured data from thousands of global sources, such as news articles, legal filings, and public records. The AI sifts through this data to highlight relevant risk factors.

Expected benefits: Provides DOJ with data to make an informed decision on whether or not to move forward with the acquisition of a good/service based on the risks identified during research. List of outputs from Exiger include:  Corporate records, beneficial owners, geopolitical risks, sanctions list, adverse media, litigation history, financial stability, supply chain relationships from a wide variety of sources"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1930 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_2,  # Ethical conduct, compliance, and leadership integrity
        aiu:BG_8_3,  # Automation and AI enablement
        aiu:BG_9_3 ;  # Resilience to geopolitical, pandemic, and disaster shocks
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Exiger DDIQ leverages natural language processing (NLP), machine learning (ML), and AI-powered analytics to enhance due diligence processes by continuously ingesting and analyzing structured and unstructured data from thousands of global sources, such as news articles, legal filings, and public records. The AI sifts through this data to highlight relevant risk factors.

Expected benefits: Provides DOJ with data to make an informed decision on whether or not to move forward with the acquisition of a good/service based on the risks identified during research. List of outputs include additional data and risk scores such as Foreign Ownership Control or Influence (FOCI), Reputational Criminal Regulatory (RCR), Financial Health Risk"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1931 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_3,  # Innovation pace and responsiveness
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Components test AWS AI tools in a test environment to assess utility. 

Expected benefits: Improves efficiencies, productivity, and data quality. Outputs vary based on the use cases."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1932 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Intelligent Recap feature within Microsoft Outlook is used for calendaring, meeting summaries, and email drafting.

Expected benefits: Reduces administrative time for user. Meeting summaries and proposed email responses."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1933 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_4,  # Customer experience, satisfaction, and retention
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The FOIA.gov Virtual Assistant Tool implements a guided workflow or wizard assisting the public in navigating the National FOIA Portal (NFP).  The solution assists in directing the public to documents agencies have made available in the public domain, to the correct agency component to submit a FOIA request, and to other content on FOIA.gov, depending on the users desired goal.

Expected benefits: The solution helps requesters and agencies by enabling the public to find the records they are seeking without the need for a FOIA request, by lessening the number of misdirected requests, and by reducing the need for agencies to respond to unnecessary or misdirected requests. The solution gives a recommendation to the user on which agency to submit a FOIA request to, or whether the desired information is already available. Users are free to ignore the recommendations and submit FOIA requests to any agency they choose."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1934 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This AI and Natural Language Processing (NLP) tool is used to assess the similarity of records schedules across all Department records schedules.  The solution's technical approach has applicability with other domains that require text similarity analysis.

Expected benefits: The tool provides clusters of similar items to significantly reduce the time that the Records Manager spends manually reviewing schedules for possible consolidation. An AI powered dashboard provides recommendations for schedule consolidation and review, while also providing the Records Manager with the ability to review by cluster or by individual record."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1935 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: NSD uses Veritone to transcribe and translate written, audio, and video files.  A standard workflow is our office receiving the media from the case team, we load it to the gov cloud, use one of the available Veritone engines to perform the transcription and/or translation, download the results, and provide back to the case team.

Expected benefits: Veritone is used to translate and transcribe non-English language audio for attorney review. This machine translation does not constitute an official record, but is a tool to allow initial review of the audio by the attorney. Veritone is also used to provide English language translations of large sets of documents containing non-English text in order to get an initial idea of the document contents and do not replace official translation of evidence. For text files that are transcribed into English the output contains the translated text. For Audio and video files a text file transcribing the translation is created as well as a closed captioning file."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1936 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: CRM Analytics Plus provides contextual insights and AI-powered predictions and insights to drive engagement and focus directly in the flow of work in Salesforce. Drive outcomes at scale and get answers to inform your next best action with intelligent recommendations for every line of business or industry. This license also includes AI features, which are not in use at this time.

Expected benefits: NSD procured CRM Analytics Plus licenses for the use of Tableau for reporting. No output. AI features not in use."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1937 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_2,  # Cybersecurity and protection
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Capture existing baseline network configuration and behavior with associated ports, protocols and services. Analyze the traffic and characterize normal ports, protocols and services. Identify any outliers and/or anomalous traffic. 

Expected benefits: Proactive monitoring, detection, and response to possible malicious activity which could disrupt OCDETF services. Also, this capability will allow OCDETF to protect the data from any malicious activity. Recommendation
Summary of ports, protocols and services in use within the network compared to defined network traffic, ports, protocols and services. The comparison displays the difference and identifies outliers as a recommendation to investigate for possibly malicious or anomalous activities."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1938 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_2,  # Cybersecurity and protection
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Capture existing baseline network configuration and behavior with associated ports, protocols and services. 

Expected benefits: Proactive monitoring, detection and response to possible malicious activity which could disrupt OCDETF services. Also, this capability will allow OCDETF to protect the data from any malicious activity. Recommendation
Summary of ports, protocols and services in use within the network compared to defined network traffic, ports, protocols and services. The comparison displays the difference and identifies outliers as a recommendation to investigate for possibly malicious or anomalous activities."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1939 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_4,  # Ethics, fraud, and whistleblowing
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Deploys predictive analytics to enhance recognition of, and highlighting of, fraudulent financial activity across OFC financial and criminal holdings. This is a PATT 3.0 process that is similar to the work being done to analyze suspicious activity reports (SARs) across federal judicial districts, currently done 1 district at a time with a manual stand-up by the OFC Search team and review by the OFC FAS, but generalized and upscaled. 

Expected benefits: Improve efficiencies by identifying and prioritizing financial fraud activity tied to open criminal investigations by including a broader data set and across multiple judicial districts to develop a better whole-of-US picture of financial fraud. List of subjects with open criminal investigations which would be worth additional manual review for financial ties."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1940 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Analyze suspicious activity reports (SAR) using generative AI functionality.  

Expected benefits: Speed up production times for providing investigative support to the field. It also allows investigative analysts to have more bandwidth to do some deeper analysis. Summarization of applicable FinCEN suspicious activity reports (SARs)."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1941 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Create charts and graphs by describing the requested data to integrate.

Expected benefits: Charts and graphs aide in reporting of OCDETF investigations. Enabling this technology will  tremendously reduce the time which was used for formatting traditional Microsoft products. Recommendation
Provide sample data to create charts and graphs to populate"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1942 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_2,  # Cybersecurity and protection
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Using generative AI modeling, we will create large volumes of test data so that QA, external audits and penetration testing, system demos & integration, etc., can use that generated test data at scale.  

Expected benefits: OCDETF developing and operating with a test set of data will enable engagements with external groups (like penetration test team, or vendors who want to see what the system looks like so they can offer a tailored demo or proposal). But manual generation of test data at the scale needed is not feasible, so we would rely on generative AI. Test Data
Sample and/or mockup of test data from the applications used within the environment"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1943 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To take into account various criteria such as analyst workloads, similarities in case narratives and targets, and regional factors to suggest the optimal routing and assignment for product requests.  

Expected benefits: Improve efficiencies in routing request for OFC Products to send to the analysts and/or analytic units most suitable for working the product. Reduce rework and streamline the approvals process by suggesting agency approvers based on automated review of the product's content and ensuring all appropriate agencies are consulted for manual review. Suggested assignment / routing for OFC Product Requests (e.g. to an analytic unit or specific analyst). Suggested approver assignments based on referenced agency data."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1944 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Identify proposed OCDETF investigations for prioritized review, approval, and potential case designation based on success criteria trained from the entire OCDETF MIS corpus.  

Expected benefits: Improve efficiencies in routing OCDETF proposals through the workflow to receive OCDETF designation. Identify the best use of resources through ML trained on investigations matching emerging threats. Lists of proposed OCDETF investigations in prioritized order."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1945 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Will create summaries or precis from large volumes of text narratives submitted on OCDETF forms, for both information triage and trend analysis / emerging threat detection purposes. Gen AI would also allow interactive queries (e.g. you ask it questions) about the data it has summarized, and would be transparent (with citations of underlying data as needed). 

Expected benefits: Provide rapid review of information submitted as data ingested into the Fusion Desktop database. This will reduce the time necessary during data entry and review and will provide guidance on emerging threat areas which OCDETF may use to determine resource allocation or areas for additional study. Summary of long narrative text (on a per form basis). Summary of trends common across multiple forms' narrative texts; e.g. if "liquid fentanyl" is a topic identified in multiple narratives over a short period of time in a specific OCDETF Region, it could indicate an emerging threat to follow up on."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1946 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Will create summaries or precis from large volumes of text narratives submitted on OCDETF forms, for both information triage and trend analysis / emerging threat detection purposes. Gen AI would also allow interactive queries (e.g. you ask it questions) about the data it has summarized, and would be transparent (with citations of underlying data as needed).

Expected benefits: Provide rapid review of information submitted on OCDETF forms, including Investigation Initiation Forms (IIFs) and interim and final updates on open investigations. This will reduce the time necessary during data entry and review for OCDETF forms and will provide guidance on emerging threat areas which OCDETF may use to determine resource allocation or areas for additional study. Summary of long narrative text (on a per form basis). Summary of trends common across multiple forms' narrative texts; e.g. if "liquid fentanyl" is a topic identified in multiple narratives over a short period of time in a specific OCDETF Region, it could indicate an emerging threat to follow up on."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1947 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Train AI on exemplary analyst work to suggest course of action to all analysts while they perform product research and development. 

Expected benefits: Improve efficiencies in developing OFC Products by providing decision support and limited automation by ML trained on exemplar analysts at the OFC. Provides guidance and suggestions particularly for resource-intensive actions, like conducting open source, commercial, or offline (swivel-chair) searches of data sets outside the OFC. Suggested actions at each phase of OFC Product development workflow."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1948 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Transcribe an audio file recordings to output a text transcript of the multiple speakers in the recording. A human validates the accuracy of transcriptions, and this tool is not used in investigations.

Expected benefits: Efficiency and cost savings. Individuals will spend less time and materials to fully process a recording and will deliver transcriptions sooner. Text file with transcription of speakers within the recording."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1949 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Analyze draft reports and provide content recommendations in compliance with published standards, guidance, and rule books.  The published standards, guidance, and rule books may define formatting, characteristics of a good report, quality guidelines, requirements, internal controls, and generally accepted principles for an area of work.  Reports and all substantive content are authored by humans, not by AI.

Expected benefits: Quicker turn around for creating reports, analysis of reports to ensure consistency in content and removal of redundancy, and to assist in the management of report length. Suggested phrases to reword a paragraph and/or identification of errors in statements as they align towards defined standards, guidance, or rule books."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1950 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Provide human-like conversational responses to conduct general information searches and suggestions towards improving text using generative artificial intelligence.

Expected benefits: Improve work efficiencies and curve user generative AI usage to an environment that is controlled and contained within GCCH and the DOJ OIG subscription instead of a commercial service.  The information and models generated within the GCCH environment stays within GCCH and do not further the model of commercial products or services. The AI provides generative AI human-like responses/answers to questions and/or statements from a user.  In addition, the output can be a generated summary of an inputted excerpt or publicly available information."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1951 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_6_1,  # Talent, skills, and workforce strategy
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The application is speech recognition software that initiates commands on a device or takes dictation into a word processing application.  The application is used for individuals with reasonable accommodations related to and/or difficulty typing, seeing, or navigating a Windows operating system environment.

Expected benefits: Increased accessibility. Dictation of spoken words into a word processing document or initiation of macro commands in the Windows operating system environment."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1952 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Informatica Enterprise Data Catalog with CLAIRE is an AI-powered data catalog that provides a machine-learning-based discovery engine to scan and catalog data assets across OIG. CLAIRE will be used to categorize, classify, and organize OIG data. It will also automate the data curation and connect data across OIG from disparate sources, and will track data movement from system views to column-level lineage. 

Expected benefits: Increases the efficiency and effectiveness by which OIG can locate and analyze our data. Recommendations about OIG data"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1953 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Law enforcement usage of Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to assist with license plate reading under DOJ Policy.  LPR data is managed and maintained by other entities for law enforcement purposes.

Expected benefits: Law enforcement usage of Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to assist with license plate reading under DOJ Policy. DOJ's National Crime Information Center (JWIN) facilitates access to the Nlets Nationwide License Plate Reader Pointer Index, which provides access to states and/or federal agencies that maintain their own LPR repositories. LPR data is managed and maintained by other entities for law enforcement purposes."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1954 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Archival capture of raw video and audio footage that are accessed only to the extent needed for prosecution or investigation purposes.  AI functionalities for analysis, voice transcription, and redaction are not utilized or relevant for our use.

Expected benefits: This use case does not utilize AI functions.  AI features are included in the product, but have not been installed and not relevant for our use. N/A; AI features not in use"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1955 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_7_4,  # Ethics, fraud, and whistleblowing
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To estimate a financial assistance awards questioned costs during an audit.

Expected benefits: Provide auditors with an additional resource in performing risk assessments that assist in the audit selection process. Allowing auditors to focus work on higher-risk grants can allow for the recovery or redirection of misused government funds and improve auditor effectiveness and efficiency. Estimated questioned costs resulting from an OIG audit."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1956 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The purpose of this AI use case is to develop a standardized approach to analyzing computer-aided dispatch (CAD) data from various law enforcement agencies. Due to the current lack of standardization in how these data are collected, the aggregation of police activity across agencies is limited and not scalable. By leveraging machine learning and large language models, the project aims to create a text classifier that standardizes raw CAD data, enabling comprehensive comparisons of police activities and community needs across jurisdictions with the goal of providing national estimates of calls for service. 

Expected benefits: The ability to standardize and better leverage agency CAD data has implications for the individual agencies, state and federal government, and the research community. From an operational perspective, use of this tool will allow for the more efficient organization of data within the agency as well as the ability to compare across agencies regionally or at the state level to compare police activity and community needs. The standardization schema and the tool's translation of data into this format serves as a shared language that can allow for jurisdictional comparisons not before possible at scale. From the DOJ's perspective, a nationally representative police CAD dataset supplements NIBRS to provide an understanding of patterns in activity not captured by NIBRS and includes police activity beyond the scope of traditional crime measures. Likewise, for the public and research community, previous understandings of police activity, how they spend their time, and issues across communities have been limited within jurisdictions. This project, supported by the AI tool, will provide an opportunity for a broader understanding of the work law enforcement does in communities. The output of the autocoder is a classification prediction. In the context of event type, it takes raw text like 'shoplifting' runs the raw code through an LLM and predicts which of our established categories that event belongs in, in this case "Property Crime: Theft". The output of the packaged tool is a dataset with these classifications appended to the raw CAD file."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1957 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: A pilot OJP Office for Victims of Crime Notice of Funding Opportunity allowed video submissions of grant applications. MS Streams transcribed videos into scripts.

Expected benefits: MS Streams transcribed videos into scripts. Transcriptions helped reviewers speed up the review process. The system outputs video transcriptions. These transcriptions informed recommendations for grant awards."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1958 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The purpose of this tool is to improve description and comparability of offense charges across jurisdictions. When using justice administrative data from various jurisdictions (localities, states, and federal), the way offenses are described (i.e., the exact text strings used) vary greatly. For example, assault and battery may be spelled out, or abbreviated in novel ways such as A&B, A & B, A+B, A?B, battery & aslt, etc. This tool is used to facilitate grouping identical concepts under one common set of offense codes. The data that BJS makes available will be aggregated or deidentified.

Expected benefits: Improved comparisons of criminal justice data The output of this autocoder is common definitions for offense charge classification. It has been trained on an offense crosswalk for the BJS National Corrections Reporting Program (NCRP) (https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/NACJD/ncrp/Offense_Code_Crosswalk.xlsx) to convert plain-text offense descriptions into classifications routinely used by the NCRP."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1959 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: This tool was developed in response to Section 3632 of the First Step Act of 2018 which required the Attorney General to develop and release a risk and needs assessment system. PATTERN predicts the likelihood of recidivism for individuals three years after release from FBOP custody.

Expected benefits: The tool provides critical information to FBOP about the risk of recidivism and possible programming needs for their population. Prediction of the risk of recidivism"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1960 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The purpose of this tool is to improve description and comparability of offense charges across jurisdictions. When using justice administrative data from various jurisdictions (localities, states, and federal), the way offenses are described (i.e., the exact text strings used) vary greatly. For example, assault and battery may be spelled out, or abbreviated in novel ways such as A&B, A & B, A+B, A?B, battery & aslt, etc. This tool is used to facilitate grouping identical concepts under one common set of offense codes. The data that BJS makes available will be aggregated. 

Expected benefits: Improved comparisons of criminal justice data. The output of this autocoder is common definitions for offense charge classification. It has been trained on an offense crosswalk for the BJS National Corrections Reporting Program (NCRP) (https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/files/NACJD/ncrp/Offense_Code_Crosswalk.xlsx) to convert plain-text offense descriptions into classifications routinely used by the NCRP."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1961 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Use natural language processing, machine learning, and artificial intelligence processes developed by a contractor to aid in screening abstracts of newly identified evaluation research for consideration in future program ratings. 

Expected benefits: This provides a more efficient method for screening large numbers of research/program evaluation study abstracts to help identify those that are appropriate for further review and analysis in producing CrimeSolutions profiles and evidence ratings. The output is a classification prediction indicating that individual abstracts pertain to studies that meet basic parameters for inclusion and further human review."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1962 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The purpose of the AI software (Veritone) is to transcribe or translate recordings into speaker separated conversations.

Expected benefits: Using Veritones AI transcription is expected to save OPR substantial amounts of money compared to our prior, routine use of court reporters to transcribe audio recordings of investigative interviews.  In addition, human transcription of OPRs audio recorded interviews typically has a two to three week turnaround to receive the transcripts back from the court reporters.  The Veritone Illuminate AI software generates transcripts within a matter of hours.  The quicker turnaround on transcription allows OPR to more efficiently and promptly complete its investigations. The output are written transcriptions of  recorded interviews which is used as an aid in the decision making of a investigation."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1963 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_1,  # Brand positioning, identity, and value communication
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Adobe has function that enables the generation of images. PAO does not use this function/feature.

Expected benefits: PAO does not use this feature/function. Images, if feature were in use"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1964 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: EEG provides real-time captioning of live events that PAO broadcasts.

Expected benefits: Greater accessibility. Compliance with law; Section 508 requires live captioning of live events, and this provides it. Captions"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1965 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_2_1,  # Brand positioning, identity, and value communication
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: PAO uses Hootsuite to schedule and manage social media products. Hootsuite also includes AI-powered social listening features, but PAO does not use those features.

Expected benefits: It can advise on when the best time to post would be for maximum engagement, which will help promote our message. Recommendations about date and time to publish content"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1966 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_4,  # Alignment with stakeholder expectations and social impact
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Social media platforms used by PAO, such as Instagram and YouTube, can automatically create video captions or alt text for images/graphics when multimedia is uploaded.

Expected benefits: Greater accessibility. It generates captions or alt text automatically in the social media platform."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1967 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Veritone Digital Media Hub includes AI features that allow PAO to search our event photo databases and identify objects in those photo catalogs.

Expected benefits: Increased efficiency of searches of archival images so that PAO can find and continue using assets. Recommendations of images that match the terms searched for"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1968 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Allows the retrieval of personal data for an individual such as historical addresses.

Expected benefits: Improve the accuracy and comprehensiveness of a clemency applicant's personal data. Summary"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1969 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Allows the retrieval of court cases and briefings.

Expected benefits: Improve accuracy and understanding of the legal issues associated with a clemency application. Summary"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1970 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Allows the retrieval of court cases when there are security concerns associated with a clemency application.

Expected benefits: Improve accuracy and understanding of the legal issues associated with a clemency application. Summary"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1971 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Allows the retrieval of court cases and briefings.

Expected benefits: Improve accuracy and understanding of the legal issues associated with a clemency application. Summary"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1972 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Allows the retrieval of personal data for an individual such as historical addresses.

Expected benefits: Improve the accuracy and comprehensiveness of a clemency applicant's personal data. Summary"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1973 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_3,  # Internal controls, procedures, and performance management
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Salient Factor Score is an actuarial risk assessment device designed in the 80's and last updated in 1998 which is based entirely on pre-incarceration factors, including prior criminal history, nature of the instant offense, age at the instant offense, and other factors.

Expected benefits: Helps assess the likelihood of success on parole.  This is one of several factors. Score"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1974 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: ProLaw assists PRAO attorneys in searching a large quantity of prior PRAO inquiries and advice stored in a database to identify relevant historical inquiry files that will assist the attorneys in determining how PRAO has advised on similar matters in the past.  

Expected benefits: ProLaw enables PRAO to store digitally all PRAO inquiry files, consistent with the component's records retention schedule.  ProLaw also enables PRAO personnel to quickly search large quantities of inquiry files to identify relevant historical inquiries and advice to a current matter a PRAO attorney is working on.  This greatly reduces the amount of time it takes PRAO staff to research which then reduces the wait time of the Department attorney who has requested PRAO advice.  Because ProLaw allows PRAO to store records digitally, it also provides a significant government cost savings in the amount of money paid to store hard copy records. ProLaw's output is information.  Specifically, PRAO uses ProLaw to identify all of the digital inquiry files in the database that are consistent with the user's selected search query.  For example, it might help a user to identify all PRAO inquiry files between the dates of January 1, 2023, and December 31, 2023, that discuss New York Rule of Professional Conduct 4.2 and the use of the case United States v. Nouri, 711 F. 3d 129."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1975 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: TAX sometimes receives audio or video for review without a text transcript.  Much of the time, TAX uses human transcription vendors to transcribe the audio to text; however, if the volume is significant, TAX might use the AWS service to transcribe to text so that it is keyword-searchable and a rough version can be evaluated by the reviewer, and it can be determined if a certified version is required.

Expected benefits: Neural machine transcription that converts audio to text. Transcribed text."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1976 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Often times, TAX receives information for review in a foreign language.  Much of the time, TAX uses human translation vendors to translate the foreign language to English; however, if the volume is significant, TAX might use the AWS service to translate the text so that it is English searchable and a rough English version can be evaluated by the reviewer and it can be determined if a certified version is required for relevant records. 

Expected benefits: Neural machine translation that provides language translation of text-based content. Translated text."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1977 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Text to speech software for the visually impaired.

Expected benefits:  Increased accessibility. Audio description of visual objects. Typically used for blind individuals and satisfies 508 requirements. Audio summaries of text"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1978 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: OnCue is a trial presentation tool.  The tool allows an operator to display exhibits (e.g., tiff, jpg, native, audio/video) onto a screen and speakers.  This tool allows users to edit video, load documents and images, and annotate (e.g., highlights, callouts, zooms).  When used as a litigation support tool, OnCue can be used to stamp records with Exhibit or Bates endorsements, for example.

Expected benefits: Facilitates efficient exhibit management. Digital images."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1979 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: TextMap is a means for displaying transcripts for review. The input is text or video, and TextMap formats the underlying transcript files for human review and markup. TAX uses this tool to organize, search and annotate text transcripts as well as link text to video testimony or exhibits. Owned by Lexis, and part of a suite that also includes CaseMap.

Expected benefits: Used to organize, search and annotate text transcripts as well as link text to video testimony or exhibits Annotated transcripts."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1980 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The AI/Axon Redaction Assistant is non-generative and used in workflow automation.  AI is used in limited capacity to blur/redact predefined shapes in Body Worn Camera (BWC) footage for release to various law enforcement entities and the public upon request.  

Expected benefits: This product allows for the protection of identities. Recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1981 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Clearview AI provides law enforcement and government agencies with lead generation through the use of a search platform. The platform includes the largest known database of 50+ billion facial images sourced from public-only web sources, including news media, mugshot websites, public social media, and many other open sources. USMS utilizes Clearview AI to search photos of known individuals against publicly available images for similar matches.

Expected benefits:  Clearview AIs investigative platform enables the rapid development, evaluation, and utilization of critical information otherwise unknown to investigators, allowing for possible investigative leads to be realized. Such crucial information assists in the swift and secure apprehension of violent fugitives and recovery of critically missing children, thereby helping to make communities safer. Clearview AI will provide a list of possible matches to a probe image. When a Clearview AI user uploads an image, the technology processes the image and returns links to publicly available images that contain faces like the person pictured in the uploaded image. This serves as an investigative lead."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1982 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_4_2,  # Supply chain, logistics, inventory, and fulfillment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Justice Prisoner and Alien Transportation System (JPATS) developed JARS to plan prisoner trips through the transportation network based on historical paths and future possibilities.

Expected benefits: Schedule prisoners to trips, reducing workload for scheduling Decision"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1983 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_2,  # Supply chain, logistics, inventory, and fulfillment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Justice Prisoner and Alien Transportation System (JPATS) developed the Route Optimizer to evaluate over 2000 possible flight options and select the most optimal flights.

Expected benefits:  Improve efficiency of JPATS though the optimal use of flight assets. Recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1984 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: To transfer image text to digital text. 

Expected benefits: Unlock new functionality, archive files, and reduce countless data entry manhours. The output would be the text characters in a string format."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1985 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The UAS AI tool is used to avoid crashing into objects. It is also used to identify if an object is a person or vehicle.

Expected benefits: Prevention of UAS crashes and identification of objects and persons from a distance. A box is drawn around the objects."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1986 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: USMS uses open source natural language processing technologies and python code to transcribe an audio or video file into plain text. 

Expected benefits: The product allows analysts to quickly convert a video or audio file to text. Transcription NLP algorithm"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1987 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: The Axon VRS Transcription Tool is an AI-powered feature within Axon's video retention solution, which automatically transcribes audio and video recordings. 

Expected benefits: The Axon VRS Transcription Tool allows users to quickly review audio and video recordings by reading and searching through text, instead of having to watch the entire footage and listen to accompanying audio. This tool essentially provides a time-synced transcript for quick and easy analysis. Computer based transcription of BWC footage into text."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1988 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: USMS uses this tool for authorized investigative lead generation which will improve efficiencies of public safety and law enforcement missions. 

Expected benefits:  More efficient screening of leads for potential investigative actions. Recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1989 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: JPATS uses biometric facial recognition software to identify prisoners in transit and pull up their movement packet for quicker and more accurate boarding of planes.

Expected benefits: Faster and more accurate prisoner identification Recommendation"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1990 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Receive biometric data and reformat for sharing in support of investigative processes. This tool is not used for biometric identification/authentication.

Expected benefits: The benefit is reducing the costs associated with manual processing of biometric data. Structured data"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1991 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Translate from French, Spanish, or Arabic into English in support of investigative processes.

Expected benefits: The benefit is reducing the costs associated with human translators. Translated text"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1992 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Use of commercial tool and the embedded technology to search through public records for investigative purposes. 

Expected benefits: The benefit is access to wide array of information. Research recommendations"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1993 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Use of commercial tool and the embedded technology to search through public records for investigative purposes. 

Expected benefits: The benefit is access to wide array of information. Research recommendations"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1994 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_7_1,  # Regulatory and legal compliance
        aiu:BG_7_4,  # Ethics, fraud, and whistleblowing
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Use of commercial tool and the embedded technology to search through public records for investigative purposes. 

Expected benefits: The benefit is access to wide array of information. Research recommendations"""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1995 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_3_3,  # Innovation pace and responsiveness
        aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: Intended purpose is to enable USTP's IT team to understand the process to develop, test, tune and use the Azure Open AI Generative AI service.  A secondary purpose is to understand the full costs and time to develop and implement a use case from start to finish.  A third purpose is to ensure the Generative AI service is providing useful responses and value give the cost and time to set up and deploy. 

Expected benefits: Intended benefits of using Azure Open AI would be to enable USTP staff to find information quickly on relevant technical questions they may have.  This use case would help reduce Help Desk calls and increase productivity, enabling users to find technical information quickly. Potential to help generate new content based on pilot testing. Generate text responses and summaries to USTP prompts."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOJ_1996 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_1,  # Technology and data alignment
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Purpose: USTP is planning to  have the vendor for our System Modernization project use Generative AI Code Assistant (e.g., GitHub Copilot, Codium, etc.) to assist in writing/reviewing code for this effort. The vendor will perform a review of the code generated and USTP will scan using various code scanning services/tools to ensure secure quality code.  All code for this project is published in USTP's public GitHub repository.

Expected benefits: USTP expects to see faster and more efficient code development for our System Modernization efforts.  Research reports based on other Agencies and Corporations shows up to a 35% increase in code development efficiencies. In addition USTP anticipates seeing fewer issues and errors as these Code Assistants will perform reviews reducing errors/bugs in code. Generate code for USTP's system modernization effort."""^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_DOL_499 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText "Custom machine learning model to extract data from complex forms to tag data entries to field headers. The input is a document or scanned image of the form and the output is a JSON response with key/value pairs extracted by running the form against the custom trained form recognition model. The AI system output is a recommendation."^^xsd:string .

