aiu:plan_2024_VA_1616 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText "To be used to personalize screening regime, calling high risk patients earlier to catch cancers in the early stages and potentially reducing screening burden for low risk patients. It takes as input a lung low-dose CT scan, and produces a JSON return object with predictions of the odds of developing cancer within the next 6 years (one prediction for each year)."^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_VA_1617 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_4_4,  # Scaling operations without degrading quality or CX
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText "eCaremanager integrates clinical, physiological, and demographic data from all patients entered into the National TeleCC Program.  The data are presented graphically to users.  Additionally, the data are used to generate acuity scores to assess each patients acuity in comparison to all other patients.  Trend and threshold alerts are also generated to notify providers to take a closer look at those patients and initiate treatments to remediate derangements and facilitate return to homeostasis and health. The outputs of eCaremanager are acuity scores and trend and threshold alerts.  The software also integrates and presents patient care information to enable providers to care for larger number of patients and provide critical care at a population level."^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_VA_1618 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_10_1,  # Product safety, data protection, and incident prevention
        aiu:BG_3_2,  # Quality, reliability, and consistency
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText "FDA-cleared medical device to assist clinicians and improve healthcare outcomes. Described in FDA documentation for this device (https://www.accessdata.fda.gov/cdrh_docs/pdf23/K231398.pdf)."^^xsd:string .

aiu:plan_2024_VA_1619 a aiu:AIUseCasePlan ;
    aiu:hasBusinessGoal aiu:BG_4_1,  # Process efficiency and waste reduction
        aiu:BG_8_3 ;  # Automation and AI enablement
    aiu:purposeBenefitsText """Policy lookup is a time-consuming task in the VA. This challenge was identified as an ideal candidate for generative AI product development. After completing AI engineering and product development training, our internal team developed a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) application that accepts policy-related questions and provides relevant answers based on Medical Center reference materials. 

Expected Benefits:
Time spent on finding/referencing facility policy decreases, increasing efficiency and employee satisfaction. 
Standardization of meeting minutes per Dayton governance structure. LLM produces feedback in text with links to the associated medical center publications."""^^xsd:string .

